(4688, 1, '2015-08-19 11:46:36', '2015-08-19 08:46:36', '[:en]<p style="text-align: justify;">Triple Plus Ltd. (the "<strong>Company</strong>”) warrants to the original purchaser of the Products from the Company (the "<strong>Purchaser</strong>"), alone, that the Products (i.e. water and/or gas management systems as were manufactured by the Company; this Warranty shall not apply to the battaries used with respect to the Products (the warranty applicable thereto shall be that issued by the battery manufacturer, to the extent issued) and any other acompanying procducts/components to the Products, will be free of defects in material and workmanship under standard use for a period of 24 months following the date the Product was delivered to such Purchaser from the Company (the "<strong>Warranty Period</strong>"), all subject to and in accordance with the terms and conditions hereof.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The Company''s sole obligation and Purchaser''s sole and exclusive remedy under this Warranty shall be limited, subject to the terms herein, to the repair and/or replacement of any defective Product (and/or any component thereof) which was proven not to conform to its respective specifications and which shall be subsequently returned to the Company''s facility during the Warranty Period (with transportation charges prepaid by the Purchaser).</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The effectiveness of this Warranty with respect to each Product shall be subject to and contingent upon the full payment of the consideration due for such Product by the Purchaser.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Purchaser must obtain a Return Material Authorization (“<strong>RMA</strong>”) number from Company prior to returning any Product to Company and must otherwise follow Company’s then-current RMA procedure in connection with any such return. If Company determines in its reasonable discretion that any Product returned by Purchaser does not conform to this Warranty (“<strong>Non-Conforming Products</strong>”), Company will notify the Purchaser of such and will return the applicable Non-Conforming Product to the Purchaser at the Purchaser’s expense. In addition, Company may assess Purchaser a charge for testing and examination of Non-Conforming Products.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">It shall be clarified that this Warranty shall not apply to any damages and/or failures and/or defects to a Product (or due to any use of Products) caused as a result of the Product installment and/or the maintenance or the lack of maintenance of the Product.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The Company does not warrant, whether expressly or implied, that the respective Product will perform uninterrupted or error free. Furthermore, this Warranty is contingent upon proper maintenance, use and storage of the Products, and does not cover any failures and/or problems of any kind and/or nature with respect to Products, or due to any use of the Products, that have been subject to (i) damage, neglect, improper storage and maintenance; (ii) abnormal use or misuse, or use in a manner not in accordance with the instructions provided by the Company, whether through acts, omissions, negligence, error or accident; (iii) tampering, change, alteration or modification by any party other than the Company (iv) improper handling or repair, storage, installation or maintenance by any person and/or entity other than the Company or not in accordance with Company instructions (v) excessive operating conditions; (vi) unusual environmental conditions; (vii) accidental or intentional damage by any person other than the Company; (viii) installation not in accordance with Company instructions or in combination or interaction with a third party component or software; or (ix) force majeure events or other event not within the control of the Company.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Furthermore, the Company does not warrant nor make any representation regarding the results of the use or omission to use the Product and/or any information or data provided by the respective Product in terms of <em>inter alia</em> correctness, accuracy, completeness, reliability or otherwise and the Company expressly disclaims all express or implied or statutory representations, warranties, guarantees and conditions with regard to the Products and/or as a result of using the Products and/or as a result of using the Products or any of its features or components (including in terms of correctness, accuracy, completeness, timeliness of the content, reliability or otherwise), including but not limited to representations, warranties, guarantees and conditions of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, title, non-infringement and/or loss of data. Without limiting the foregoing, the Company does not represent or warrant that the operation or use of the Products will be timely, secure, uninterrupted or error free.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">IN NO EVENT AND NOTWITHSTANDING ANYTHING TO THE CONTRARY HEREIN AND/OR UNDER ANY APPLICABLE LAW OR CONTRACT, WILL THE COMPANY, ITS SHAREHOLDERS, DIRECTORS, OFFICERS, EMPLOYEES OR ANY PARTY ON THEIR BEHALF BE LIABLE TO PURCHASER OR ANY OTHER PARTY FOR ANY INDIRECT DAMAGES, LOSSES AND LIABILITIES, INCLUDING WITHOUT LIMITATION LOSS OF PROFIT, CONSEQUENTIAL, INCIDENTAL, PUNITIVE, SPECIAL OR EXEMPLARY DAMAGES CAUSED OR ARISING, DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY, IN CONNECTION WITH THIS WARRANTY OR USE OR INABILITY TO USE THE PRODUCTS (INCLUDING WITHOUT LIMITAIONS, DAMAGES TO PROPERTY OR TO THE PRODUCTS, DAMAGES FOR LOST INFORMATIONS, LOST SAVINGS, LOST PROFITS OR BUSINESS INTERRUPTION) EVEN IF THE COMPANY HAS BEEN INFORMED, IS AWARE, OR SHOULD BE OR HAS BEEN AWARE, OF THE POSSIBILTY OF SUCH DAMAGES. THE PURCHASER INCLUDING THE CUSTOMER ASSUMES SOLE RISK AND SHALL BE SOLELY RESPONSIBLE FOR EVALUATING, ANALYZING AND USING THE PRODUCT OR THE DATA PROVIDED BY THE PRODUCT, AND THE COMPANY SHALL IN NO EVENT BE